Jolin Tsai concert tours

Tsai performing during the Dancing Forever World Tour in Singapore, April 2007
↙Concert tours 4
↙One-off concerts 21

Taiwanese singer Jolin Tsai (Chinese: 蔡依林) has embarked on four concert tours, each of which has been worldwide. Her 2004 debut, the J1 World Tour, was based in Asia and visited North America.[1] Tsai appeared onstage on a rising platform and stroke yoga poses.[2] In 2006, Tsai performed on the Dancing Forever World Tour, which visited Asia, Oceania, and North America. The performances featured Tsai striking yoga poses on rings and pommel horse.[3] However, some critics complained that the show concentrated on "juggling", but generally the response was favorable, with over 500,000 ticket sales.[4] In 2010, she embarked on the Myself World Tour. The performances featured Tsai performing either aerial hoop or pole dance during the final segment.[5] She grossed more than NT$150 million and eventually played in front of 600,000 people in Asia, Europe, and Oceania.[6] In 2015, Tsai performed on the Play World Tour, which collaborated with Live Nation Entertainment and visited Asia and North America.[7]
